            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In n(omine) D(omi)ni. Const[a]t me <persName key="#Deacons #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#people/1554">Andreas</persName> gr(aci)a D(e)i <rs key="#Deacons"
                            >diacon(us)</rs> et <rs key="#Monks">monachus</rs> atq(ue) <rs
                            key="#Abbots">abb(as)</rs> regul(e) <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >mon(asterii)</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Deacons #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1487">S(an)c(t)i Apo[le]naris q(ui) vec(atur)
                            Novo</orgName> accepissem et accepi at vob(is) <persName><name
                                ref="Apollinaris">Apol(e)naris</name></persName> filio quond(am)
                                <persName><name ref="Iohannes">Ioh(anni)s</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Rent_in_money">pensione(m)</rs> p(ro) <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">tres uncias</rs> integ(ras) q(ui) e(st)
                        pos(ita) in <rs key="#Fundi">fundu(m)</rs> q(ui) voc(atur) <geogName
                            key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Rent_in_money" ref="#estates/2421"
                                ><placeName key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Rent_in_money"
                                >Colopedio</placeName></geogName> cu(m) om(n)ib(us) sibi
                        pertinentibus, teritorio <geogName key="#Fundi #Fines" ref="#estates/2422"
                                ><placeName key="#Fundi #Fines" ref="#places/3515"
                                >Liviense</placeName></geogName>, <rs key="#Plebs">pl(e)be</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Plebs" ref="#juridical_persons/1488">S(an)c(t)e
                            Reparate</orgName>, qu[as] p(er) <rs
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">enfiteusin</rs> tenere viso estis
                        at iure s(uprascrip)ti mon(asterii) n(ost)ri, et p(er) unaquaque
                        ind(i)ccione d(e)[n]arii q(ui)nq(ue) tantu(m). Und(e) p(ro) munimine
                        v(est)ri feci vob(is) hoc d(e)acepto in m(en)se mar(cio), ind(i)cc(ione)
                        septima, <placeName ref="#places/594">Rav(enne)</placeName>. Andreas
                        di(a)c(onus) et abb(a) mon(asterii) S(an)c(t)i Apolen(aris) in ct
                        deacdeaceto s(ub)s(cripsi).</ab>
